==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Meconidium
<hw>Mec`o*nid"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., dim.
of Gr. <?/ a poppy. So called in allusion to the shape of the seed
capsules of the poppy.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A kind of
gonophore produced by hydroids of the genus <gen>Gonothyraea</gen>. It
has tentacles, and otherwise resembles a free medusa, but remains
attached by a pedicel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meconin</ent>⟦br⟧
